print('Microsoft Copilot serves as an AI-powered assistant integrated with various Microsoft tools, enabling users to leverage generative AI for enhanced productivity and creativity. Here’s a brief overview of how to use it effectively:\n\n1. **Accessing Copilot**: \n   - Users must sign in with a Microsoft Entra account to access Copilot.\n   - It can be accessed via the Copilot site (copilot.cloud.microsoft) or directly within Microsoft 365 applications such as Word, Excel, and PowerPoint【4:0†source】.\n\n2. **User Interface**:\n   - The interface includes a simplified chat model where users can input prompts.\n   - Recent chats and suggested prompts are accessible from the sidebar【4:0†source】【4:1†source】.\n\n3. **Functionality**:\n   - **Chat Interactions**: Users can ask questions or input commands to receive insights, summaries, and various forms of data manipulation.\n   - **File Uploads**: Users can upload files (like PDFs or Excel sheets) for Copilot to analyze and provide detailed insights or summarization【4:2†source】【4:3†source】.\n   - **Previous Chats**: Users can refer back to past interactions to continue discussions or rethink prompts【4:2†source】.\n\n4. **Enterprise Data Protection (EDP)**:\n   - Copilot offers EDP for users signed in with a Microsoft Entra account, ensuring that data is protected and not used to train AI models.\n   - The interface reassures users of data protection features with the presence of a shield icon【4:0†source】【4:5†source】.\n\n5. **Recommended Practices**:\n   - For an optimal experience, it’s advised to provide clear prompts, use specific terminology, and engage with the chat to refine outputs.\n   - Keep an eye on updates as new capabilities and features like image uploading and contextual prompt suggestions are expected to roll out【4:2†source】【4:4†source】.\n\nFor further details, refer to the official documentation or the Copilot learning hub provided by Microsoft.')

